org.threadly.litesockets

Interface UDPServer.UDPReader

  • Enclosing class:
    UDPServer

    public static interface UDPServer.UDPReader
    The UDPServer UDPReader. If a UDPReader is set on a UDPServer every read from the socket will call onUDPRead before being passed to a UDPClient. If false is returned the UDPPacket will not be sent to the UDPClient, if true, then it will be.

      • onUDPRead

        boolean onUDPRead(java.nio.ByteBuffer bb,
                  java.net.InetSocketAddress isa)
        This is called whenever the UDPServer reads data from the socket.
        Parameters:
        bb - the ByteBuffer containing the data from the read.
        isa - the SocketAddress of who sent the data.
        Returns:
        true if the data should be passed onto the UDPClient, false if it should not be.
